{"info": {"author": "Daniel Poland", "author_email": "dan@crispy.dev", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Framework :: Pytest", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "description": "# slacktools-slackfixtures\n\nA pytest plugin that adds useful fixtures for testing Slack integrations.\n\n#### Install:\n`pip install slacktools-slackfixtures`\n\n#### Example usage:\n```python\nfrom myapp.tasks import post_message\n\n\ndef test_post_message(mock_slack):\n    response_data = {\"status\": \"OK\"}\n    slack = mock_slack(path=\"myapp.tasks.slack\", method=\"chat_postMessage\", response_data=response_data)\n    response = post_message()\n\n    slack.chat_postMessage.assert_called_once()\n    assert response.data == response_data\n```\n\n#### Test for failure:\n\n```python\nimport pytest\nfrom slack.errors import SlackApiError\n\nfrom myapp.tasks import post_message\n\n\ndef test_post_message_failure(mock_slack):\n    response_data = {\"status\": \"Not OK\"}\n    slack = mock_slack(\n        path=\"myapp.tasks.slack\",\n        method=\"chat_postMessage\", \n        response_data=response_data, \n        validates=False\n    )\n    response = post_message()\n\n    with pytest.raises(SlackApiError):\n        response.validate()\n```\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/danpoland/slacktools-slackfixtures", "keywords": "", "license": "", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "slacktools-slackfixtures", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/slacktools-slackfixtures/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/slacktools-slackfixtures/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/danpoland/slacktools-slackfixtures"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/slacktools-slackfixtures/1.0.0/", "requires_dist": ["pytest (~=5.3.5)", "pytest-mock (~=2.0.0)", "slackclient (~=2.5.0)"], "requires_python": ">=3.6", "summary": "", "version": "1.0.0", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>slacktools-slackfixtures</h1>\n<p>A pytest plugin that adds useful fixtures for testing Slack integrations.</p>\n<h4>Install:</h4>\n<p><code>pip install slacktools-slackfixtures</code></p>\n<h4>Example usage:</h4>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">myapp.tasks</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">post_message</span>\n\n\n<span class=\"k\">def</span> <span class=\"nf\">test_post_message</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">mock_slack</span><span class=\"p\">):</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">response_data</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"s2\">\"status\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"OK\"</span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">slack</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">mock_slack</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">path</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"s2\">\"myapp.tasks.slack\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">method</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"s2\">\"chat_postMessage\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">response_data</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"n\">response_data</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">response</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">post_message</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n\n    <span class=\"n\">slack</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">chat_postMessage</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">assert_called_once</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n    <span class=\"k\">assert</span> <span class=\"n\">response</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">data</span> <span class=\"o\">==</span> <span class=\"n\">response_data</span>\n</pre>\n<h4>Test for failure:</h4>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"nn\">pytest</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">slack.errors</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">SlackApiError</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">myapp.tasks</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">post_message</span>\n\n\n<span class=\"k\">def</span> <span class=\"nf\">test_post_message_failure</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">mock_slack</span><span class=\"p\">):</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">response_data</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"s2\">\"status\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"Not OK\"</span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">slack</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">mock_slack</span><span class=\"p\">(</span>\n        <span class=\"n\">path</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"s2\">\"myapp.tasks.slack\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n        <span class=\"n\">method</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"s2\">\"chat_postMessage\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> \n        <span class=\"n\">response_data</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"n\">response_data</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> \n        <span class=\"n\">validates</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"kc\">False</span>\n    <span class=\"p\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">response</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">post_message</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n\n    <span class=\"k\">with</span> <span class=\"n\">pytest</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">raises</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">SlackApiError</span><span class=\"p\">):</span>\n        <span class=\"n\">response</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">validate</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n</pre>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6722